# 68_welcome_scott_bug — s288 m3, the welcome-demo's first real test.
#
# m2 proved the phantom-overlay Pen-path performance works on one
# hand-coded curve. m3 takes the next step: feed in an actual SVG file
# and watch the orchestrator chain multiple performances back-to-back.
#
# This script runs the welcome animator over the real scott-bug.svg —
# Scott's avatar, ~235 anchors across 3 paths, the design case for the
# eventual welcome ceremony. By orchestration end, the doc has three
# committed Path SceneNodes with the bug's original fill/stroke colours,
# ready to be inspected or edited.
#
# ── Speed parameter ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# The smoke runs at speed=0.3 (kinetic — about 30 seconds end-to-end)
# rather than speed=1.0 (~90 seconds) so iteration during dev is
# practical. The eventual production welcome will run at 1.0 or the
# user's chosen slider value.
#
# ── Path resolution ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# SvgParser uses std::ifstream which resolves against the current
# working directory. Scott runs Curvz from the project root, so the
# relative path `resources/help/img/scott-bug.svg` works. If running
# from elsewhere, edit to an absolute path.
#
# ── Three-channel acceptance ─────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Trace channel: script dispatches `ok`; no error lines.
#
# Visual channel (THE load-bearing channel for m3): canvas shows three
#   Pen performances in sequence:
#     1. The big blue bug-body silhouette draws first — the longest
#        performance, ~half the total duration. Many anchors with their
#        out-handles extending, segments growing between them.
#     2. After a small inter-path breath (~200ms × 0.3 = 60ms), the
#        white inner highlight begins drawing.
#     3. After another breath, the dark facial-features path begins.
#   By the end, the canvas has the recognisable Scott-bug avatar in
#   full colour — outline + fill + stroke from the SVG source.
#
# Build channel: Scott's compile.
#
# ── m3 deliberate non-goals (recap) ──────────────────────────────────────
#
# - Humanization variance (per-beat wobble, considered pauses) — m4+.
# - View-mode crossfade or fade-delete — Phase-3 work, m5+.
# - Single-verb gift surface (`app.animate_svg <name>` with alias
#   resolution) — that's what wraps this when the welcome ceremony
#   lands.
# - Skip-on-replay handling — m3 will play in full every time.

#[sub] === Phase 1: List the app verbs (sanity) ===

list

#[sub] === Phase 2: Animate the scott-bug ===
#[sub] Relative path from the project root. SvgParser parses the file,
#[sub] walks the tree, the orchestrator enqueues one performance per
#[sub] Path SceneNode, plays the queue back-to-back. Returns immediately.

app animate_svg "resources/help/img/scott-bug.svg" 0.3

#[sub] === Script-end ===
#[sub] Animation continues on the main loop for ~30 seconds. Scott
#[sub] watches the bug construct itself path by path, then has a
#[sub] real fully-painted Scott-bug on canvas to inspect.
